Class PriorityQueueNode<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • projects.spatial.knnutils.PriorityQueueNode<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of element contained in the PriorityQueueNode.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<PriorityQueueNode<T>>
    public class PriorityQueueNode<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<PriorityQueueNode<T>>

    A PriorityQueueNode is a Comparable type which is used to wrap around the (data, priority) pairs in a PriorityQueue. Its overriding of the Comparable.compareTo(Object) method allows the PriorityQueue to disambiguate between the same priority elements, thus establishing a strict natural ordering inside the data structure.

    YOU SHOULD ***NOT*** EDIT THIS CLASS! If you do, you risk not passing our tests!

      • PriorityQueueNode

        public PriorityQueueNode​(T data,
                         java.math.BigDecimal priority,
                         int insertionOrder)
        3-arg constructor.
        Parameters:
        data - The element of type T held by the container.
        priority - The element's priority, as provided by the caller. "Smaller"priorities are considered "higher. The accuracy of priorities is BigDecimal, a data type that represents arbitrary precision floating point numbers.
        insertionOrder - The order that the element was inserted in, as provided by the caller. This parameter is important because, in a PriorityQueue, tie-breakers between elements with the same priority are determined by their insertion order in the PriorityQueue. It is the caller's responsibility to ensure that this parameter is passed correctly.
